name: The Flight of Osiris as he dips into Hell
description:
After Osiris' brief sojourn into the time and space of castle Gormenghast where, it is believed, Osiris oversaw the creation into spacetime of 'The Thing', Osiris returned finally to Hell in order to take charge of all Dark Art events

It is not known how this image came to be in existence but the rapid duplication ensured that all Generatives were at least aware of Osiris' presence, even if the lack of tangible activity around the birthplace of The Thing means there is little or no other observations of Osiris recorded

However, there is a strong belief within the forces of the Generatives that the bringing forth of Osiris is directly linked to the Disruptive Element in the corridor of Castle Gormenghast that birthed a subtle fracture of 'The Fabric' (which is also marked by the image of Otoris in OBJKT#491821) and provided the energy needed for the creation of 'The Thing'; it is now believed that Osiris was that energy and the fracture of The Fabric provided a direct Gateway to Hell

Otoris was unable to extract any information from the Disruptive Element before it was disengaged, but information from the Neural Network now suggests that the armies of the Disruptives are preparing for a colossal event; what that is, is not yet known




To celebrate H=N reaching half a million mints, here's my Dark Art piece for #HEN500K 

PNG 5000 x 5000  ||  November 04 2021  ||  Created by Dark Art Studio in collaboration with AI and multiple threads of a neural network and added to #HEN500K
